queues

Class Queue<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • queues.LinkedList<E>
      • queues.Queue<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>

    public class Queue<E>
extends LinkedList<E>
    Parameterized class representing a Queue which implements Iterable. Queue is a FIFO (First In First Out) data structure Objects of type Queue manage items in a singly linked list where we can enqueue() items to the end and dequeue() items from the front of the queue.
    Author:
    anuva

      • dequeue

        public E dequeue()
        Method to remove an element from the head of the queue. Receives no arguments and removes the item from the front of the queue. This method should return the generic item dequeue-ed. This method should throw an NoSuchElementException if the queue is empty.
        Returns:
        the generic item dequeue-ed or throws NoSuchElementException if attempt is made to dequeue from an empty queue.

      • peek

        public E peek()
        Method looks at the head of the queue for the least recently added item of the queue and returns an object of the generic type for the data seen at the front of the queue. The item is not removed from the front of the queue.
        Overrides:
